<%- content_for :title, "Koi Styleguide: Buttons" -%>

<%- content_for :side do -%>
  <%= render "sidebar" -%>
<%- end -%>

<div class="spacing">

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Buttons</h2>
    <p>These are the currently available button classes available in Koi:</p>
  </div>

  <div class="spacing-xxxxx-tight">
    <div><a href="#" class="button">button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__back">button__back</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary">button__primary</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__save-continue">button__save-continue</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__save">button__save</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__confirm">button__confirm</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__error">button__error</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__cancel">button__cancel</a></div>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Line Buttons</h2>
    <p>There are line button clases as well, but rarely used:</p>
  </div>

  <div class="spacing-xxxxx-tight">
    <div><a href="#" class="button__line">button__line</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__confirm__line">button__confirm__line</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__cancel__line">button__cancel__line</a></div>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Pills</h2>
    <p>Non-interactive butons:</p>
  </div>

  <div class="spacing-xxx-tight">
    <div><span class="button__pill">button__pill</span></div>
    <div><span class="button__pill__confirm">button__pill__confirm</span></div>
    <div><span class="button__pill__error">button__pill__error</span></div>
    <div><span class="button__pill__warning">button__pill__warning</span></div>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Modifiers</h2>
    <p>There are a couple of button modifier classes:</p>
  </div>

  <div class="spacing-xxx-tight">
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary button__large">button__large</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary button__small">button__small</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary button__depressed">button__depressed</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary button__full">button__full</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary button__disabled">button__disabled</a></div>
  </div>

  <p>The disabled button styles also automatically apply to buttons that have the <code>disabled</code> attribute, no extra classes needed:</p>

  <div class="spacing-xxx-tight">
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary" disabled>disabled button</a></div>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Icons</h2>
    <p>You can use <code>button__icon-left</code> or <code>button__icon-right</code> class to use an icon in a button:</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <button class="button__icon-left button__primary"><%= icon("comment") -%> Comment</button>
    <button class="button__icon-right button__primary"><%= icon("link") -%> Link</button>
  </div>

  <p>Or you can use <code>button__icon</code> to have a button with just an icon in it:</p>

  <div>
    <button class="button__icon button__primary"><%= icon("heart") -%></button>
    <button class="button__icon button__save"><%= icon("zoom_in") -%></button>
    <button class="button__icon button__error"><%= icon("home") -%></button>
    <button class="button__icon button__primary" disabled><%= icon("spinner") -%></button>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <div class="content-spacing">
    <h2 class="heading-two">Button Grouping</h2>
    <p>The <code>button-group</code> class will create consistent spacing no matter how large or small the area for the buttons are. Note as you make your window smaller the spacing around the buttons stays the same:</p>
  </div>

  <div class="button-group">
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary">Button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__secondary">Button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary">Button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary">Button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary">Button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__confirm">Button</a></div>
    <div><a href="#" class="button__primary">Button</a></div>
  </div>

</div>